  "prompt": "How do I print an application form on the OJAS website?",
  "response": "To print an application form from the OJAS website, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Visit the Official OJAS Website**: Go to the OJAS website by typing `https://ojas.gujarat.gov.in/` into your browser\u2019s address bar.\n\n2. **Login to Your Account**: If you have already registered, use your login credentials (username and password) to log in. If you haven't registered yet, you need to create an account first.\n\n3. **Go to 'My Application' Section**: Once you are logged in, navigate to the 'My Application' section. Here, you will see a list of all the applications you have submitted.\n\n4. **Select Your Application**: Find the application form you wish to print. Applications are generally listed with their respective dates, job titles, and application numbers.\n\n5. **Print Your Application**:\n    - Click on the relevant application to open it.\n    - Look for a 'Print' or 'Download' button. This is usually provided within the application details page or as an option next to the application listings.\n    - Click 'Print' or 'Download'. If you select 'Print', it will open a print dialog where you can choose your printer and print settings. If you select 'Download', it will likely save the application as a PDF which you can then open and print from your PDF viewer.\n\n6. **Verify and Print**: Ensure that the document opens correctly and verify all the details before sending it to the printer.\n\nIf you encounter any issues or if there is no direct print option available, you can:\n- **Check for Browser Print Options**: You can use your browser's print functionality by going to 'File' > 'Print' or pressing `Ctrl + P` on Windows or `Command + P` on Mac to bring up the print dialog box.\n- **Contact OJAS Support**: If the issue persists, contact the OJAS support team for assistance.\n\nMake sure you are printing the final version of your application form and all necessary details are correct before printing. If needed, you might want to save a digital copy for your records.",
